      • getPlayerNamesTabComplete

        public List<String> getPlayerNamesTabComplete(Stream<? extends net.md_5.bungee.api.connection.ProxiedPlayer> players,
                                              String[] args)
        Description copied from interface: PlatformTabCompletion
        Gets tab completions based on player names matching the command arguments.

        The returned list is unsorted by default.
        For sorting, use:
        * PlatformTabCompletion.getPlayerNamesTabCompleteSorted(Stream, String[]) for natural ordering
        * PlatformTabCompletion.getPlayerNamesTabCompleteSorted(Stream, String[], Comparator) to specify a Comparator
        Parameters:
        players - a stream of players
        args - the command arguments
        Returns:
        an unsorted list of matching names

      • getCommandSendersTabComplete

        public List<String> getCommandSendersTabComplete(Stream<net.md_5.bungee.api.CommandSender> senders,
                                                 String consoleRepresentation,
                                                 String[] args)
        Description copied from interface: PlatformTabCompletion
        Gets tab completions based on command senders matching the command argument.
        This is similar to PlatformTabCompletion.getPlayerNamesTabComplete(Stream, String[]), however, it includes the console as a possible choice. The representation of the console as a string is passed as a parameter.
        When matching against the stream of command senders, each command sender is evaluated to a String; if the command sender is a player, the player name is used. Otherwise, the console representation parameter is used.
        Parameters:
        senders - a stream of command senders
        consoleRepresentation - the string based representation of nonplayer command senders
        args - the command arguments
        Returns:
        an unsorted list of matching names
